original: DOL.FE, Gustav, Kapten, Direktör, Göteborg, f Nittorp, Älvsb l, 11/4 90 av dåv lantbr.insp, sedermera grhdl And D o Jenny Johansson, gm Asta Jansson. Studex Gbgs Real-lärov 10, inskr v CTH 11 o v GbHS 14. Resoff v Fortif 12, krigsmobil Bodens fästning 14 o 39, kapt i res v Ing.trupperna. Huvud-deläg i fma Dolfe & Co i Gbg (smör, ost, ägg, margarin o honung samt smör- o äggexp; start 00), kgl hovlev 24, vkst dir i Dolfe & CoAB sed. grund 33, inneh tillika Dolfes Smöraffär i Grästorp (grund 34). Ag fastigh i Gbg samt lantställe. Rev i Gbgs hdlskamm. Ordf i Kommunalföreningarnas Samorg i Gbg o i Fp:s lia valkrets där. Frimurare.
translated: DOL.FE, Gustav, Captain, Director, Gothenburg, born in Nittorp, Älvsborg county, on April 11th, 1890, son of the late agricultural inspector And D and Jenny Johansson. Married to Asta Jansson. Graduated from Gothenburg Real School in 1910, enrolled at Chalmers University of Technology in 1911 and Gothenburg Handelsskola in 1914. Reserve officer at Fortif from 1912, called to military service at Boden Fortress in 1914 and 1939, captain in the reserve infantry. Main owner of the company Dolfe & Co in Gothenburg (butter, cheese, eggs, margarine, and honey, as well as butter and egg exports; established in 1900), appointed royal court supplier in 1924, managing director of Dolfe & Co AB since its foundation in 1933, also owner of Dolfes Smöraffär in Grästorp (established in 1934). Owned properties in Gothenburg and a country estate. Member of the board of the Gothenburg Chamber of Commerce. Chairman of the Municipal Associations' Joint Organization in Gothenburg and the Liberal People's Party in the local constituency. Freemason.
